Runs in a loop — keeps accepting calculations until the user types "quit"
Accepts input in the format: number operator number (e.g., 10 + 5)
Supports +, -, *, /
Handles division by zero gracefully
If the input format is invalid, print an error and let the user try again (do not crash)

SOLUTION:

while True:
  user_input = input("Enter calculation (or quit): ")

  if user_input.lower() == "quit":
    print("Goodbye")
    break

  format = user_input.split()

  if len(format) != 3:
    print("Invalid format. Use: number operator number")
    continue

  num1, operator, num2 = format

  if not (num1.replace(".", "", 1).isdigit() and num2.replace(".", "", 1).isdigit()):
    print("Numbers are invalid.")
    continue

  num1 = float(num1)
  num2 = float(num2)

  if operator == "+":
    print("result =", num1 + num2)
  elif operator == "-":
    print("result =", num1 - num2)
  elif operator == "*":
    print("result =", num1 * num2)
  elif operator == "/":
    if num2 == 0:
      print("Error. Zero division")
      continue
    print("result =", num1 / num2)
  else:
    print("Invalid operator. Use: +, -, *, /")
